    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-red-pepper-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-red-pepper-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> to the pan and cook for 5-6 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-red-pepper-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>fresh</strong> <strong>tagliatelle</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the tagliatelle for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tagliatelle</strong>, reserving 175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-red-pepper-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pepper has softened, reduce the heat to medium-high and add the<strong> sliced garlic</strong> and your <strong>'Nduja </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan</p><p>Cook for a further 3-4 min, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Tip: Keep the heat medium to avoid the 'Nduja from smoking!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-red-pepper-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, remove the pan from the heat and add your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, <strong>balsamic sun-dried tomato paste</strong> and <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>with the <strong>reserved starchy pasta water </strong>and mix it all together</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-red-pepper-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> drained tagliatelle</strong> to the pan with a little <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your<strong> creamy 'Nduja & red pepper sauce with fresh tagliatelle</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-red-pepper-sauce-with-fresh-tagliatelle/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy 'Nduja & red pepper sauce with fresh tagliatelle </strong>with the <strong>salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the salad with a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
